# Python/Flask/Stripe Development Rules

## Code Style
- Use Python 3 conventions and type hints where appropriate
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use meaningful variable and function names

## Flask Best Practices
- Use environment variables for configuration (via .env file)
- Handle errors appropriately with proper HTTP status codes
- Keep routes focused and minimal

## Stripe API
- Always use environment variables for API keys (never hardcode)
- Handle Stripe exceptions appropriately
- Use webhook signature verification for payment notifications
- Test with Stripe test mode keys

## General
- Keep code simple and readable for a proof of concept
- Document API endpoints with clear comments
- Use python-dotenv to load environment variables from .env file

